          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>National Homeowners Bill of Rights Act of 2017 </b></p> <p>This bill requires servicers of federally related mortgage loans to (1) establish for each borrower's account a single electronic record accessible throughout the servicer and available to all relevant staff;&nbsp;(2) maintain a website where borrowers may check their estimated net present value; and (3) provide free interpretation services to borrowers.</p> <p>The bill also (1) establishes a loan-modification process to reduce the payments of eligible borrowers, (2) directs the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau to appoint a Mortgage Servicer Ombudsman, and (3) establishes&nbsp;certain limits on foreclosure sales.</p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDate>2017-06-22</actionDate>
        </item>
